properties.information:

properties.description: Gateway Upgrade North project
properties.information:
As part of the Gateway Upgrade North project, work is being undertaken to upgrade Depot Road from two lanes to four between Braun Street and the Gateway Motorway ramps. 

From late April 2017 for approximately eight months, both directions of traffic on Depot Road under the Gateway Motorway bridges will be temporarily realigned onto one side of the road at a time, with one lane maintained in each direction. The closed side of the road will be an active work area. 

There will also be changed traffic conditions including reduced speed limits, intermittent road shoulder/lane closures and short-term traffic stoppages required at times. Police/traffic controllers will be in place to direct motorists when required.
 
For more information, please contact the project team on 1800 607 755 or via email at contactus@gatewayupgradenorth.com.au

The work is expected to commence mid-April 2017 and finish late August 2017, weather and construction conditions permitting. This work will be undertaken Monday to Friday from 6am to 6pm and some Saturdays (as required) from 6am to 6pm.

For further information contact the project team at metropolitanregion@tmr.qld.gov.au or 13 QGOV, during business hours.

This will finalise local works undertaken as part of the New Generation Rollingstock (NGR) project. Construction hours will be from 7:00am to 5:00pm. properties.description: Between RNA Tunnel and Victoria Park  Road
properties.information:
Work is underway to widen the Inner City Bypass (ICB) from three to four lanes in each direction between Legacy Way and the RNA Tunnel.

As part of these works, there will be changed traffic conditions, including speed limit changes and lane reductions.

In the eastbound direction, traffic is moved towards the southern (centre median) side of the road, while the speed limit is reduced to 60 km/h between Legacy Way and the RNA Tunnel, and 70 km/h in the RNA Tunnel.

Westbound traffic changes will come into effect on 10 July, when ICB lanes in that direction will be reduced to one lane for a short section just prior to the AirportLink and Clem7 merge, and three lanes on the approach to the RNA tunnel. 

Westbound speed limits will be reduced to 50 km/h between the RNA Tunnel approach and the tunnel exit, and 60km/h between the RNA Tunnel and Legacy Way.

For more information, visit Brisbane City Council's website at www.brisbane.qld.gov.au or phone 3403 8888

properties.description: Between Mellum Creek and Ewan Maddock Dam
properties.information:
The Department of Transport and Main Roads (TMR) advises that works will soon begin to rehabilitate 2.3km of Steve Irwin Way, between Mellum Creek and Ewan Maddock Dam, Landsborough. Works will involve the removal of the existing road surface, resurfacing of the road and linemarking. The project is scheduled to commence from late August 2017 and take approximately eight weeks to complete, weather permitting. 
The works will be undertaken at night, between 7pm and 5am, Sunday to Thursday to avoid high traffic volumes during the day. Residents and businesses will be advised of the potential impacts, including noise, dust, vibration and intermittent access restrictions. Motorists may experience delays during these works. Lane closures, traffic controllers, reduced speed limits and road signage will be in place to ensure the safety of motorists and road workers. Variable Message Signs will also be used before the work starts. Priority access and entry through work zone for emergency cars.
